&lt;p>After a lot of research and procrastination, I finally bought a sports watch earlier this year. Pictured here, it&amp;rsquo;s a &lt;a href="https://www.garmin.com/en-GB/p/735626/pn/010-02539-13" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Garmin Fenix 7S Solar (black)&lt;/a>. I&amp;rsquo;m very happy with it, but was curious when rumours of Apple&amp;rsquo;s new sports watch began to surface.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Update 02 October 2022 - early reviews have largely confirmed the positive and negative points I discuss in this post, and most seem to agree that the Ultra is both pretty big, and aimed primarily at smartwatch users who want an upgrade from the Apple Watch in terms of battery life and rugged design.&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>A &lt;a href="https://www.ifixit.com/News/65598/apple-watch-ultra-is-beautiful-rugged-and-repairability-is-just-within-reach" target="_blank" rel="noopener">teardown by iFixit&lt;/a> shows the battery capacity at 2.1 Wh - identical to Garmin&amp;rsquo;s biggest watch, the 51mm &lt;a href="http://www.f-blog.info/garmin-fenix-7x-solar-teardown-non-destructive/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Fenix 7X&lt;/a>, which runs a month of normal use and somewhere around 100 hours of full GPS. My 42mm Fenix 7S battery is 42% of the Ultra&amp;rsquo;s capacity and has similar GPS endurance - as you might expect, given the different experience the Ultra is offering.&lt;/strong>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>New test gear: Oscilloscope and signal generator</title><link>https://jonsaville.com/post/2021/02/new-test-gear/</link><pubDate>Sat, 20 Feb 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://jonsaville.com/post/2021/02/new-test-gear/</guid><description>&lt;p>I finally gave in and bought an oscilloscope, the &lt;a href="https://www.siglenteu.com/digital-oscilloscopes/sds1000x-e-series-super-phosphor-oscilloscopes/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Siglent SDS1104X-E&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>












































































 




